records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

AS TO COUNT 1:

Defendant sentenced to serve 125 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 0 (zero) days time served.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 year.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
    
    *   Obtain and maintain employment or.
          actively looking.
    *   No firearms; weapons
    *   No criminal conduct rising to the level of probable cause by judicial officer.
    *   Pay all mandatory costs and surcharges during the 
          period of probation.  
          Any remaining balance at the end of probation will be due  
          immediately or an entry of a civil judgment.
          .
Court will consider motion for expungement if defendant pays the cost successfully completes the sentence and has no further violations of the law raising to the level of probable cause of judicial officer.
